	- advantages of Mongoose
		- naming conventions
			- note the collection name is "users" from `mongoose.model("User", userSchema);`
		- type validation
			- add `age: 34`
				- note that it is not saved in the database
					- since `age` is not in the schema
			- add `age: Number`
				- note that it is saved now
			- change age to string "whatever"
				- note that it gets a validation error
			- change age to string "34"
				- note that it is silently converted to a number
					- since the type is forced
			- change name to a number
				- note that it is casted to a string
					- since the type is forced
		- required fields
			- leave username out
				- note it saves without username
				- change: `username: {type: String, required: true},`
				- note that it does not save
					- since the schema now requires username
				- add username again
					- note that it now saves
