- basic info
	- styled-components enables you to easily combine JavaScript with styles in order to make style dynamic based on code
	- styled-components are used when you need to change the styling on the site dynamically
	- one can of course do this with embedded dynamic styles such as
		--------------------------------------------
		<div style={{display: choice !== 'der' && 'none'}}>DER is selected</div>
		--------------------------------------------
	- but styled-components has the advantage that it:
		- enables you to extract the main business logic out of JSX where it becomes increasingly convoluted as complexity increases
		- offers many more features, see [styled-components.com/docs](https://styled-components.com/docs)
	- not that one does not need to choose between styled-components and Sass but can use them both:
		- Sass for static styling application wide
		- styled-components for dynamic styling within a specific component
