- this howto shows you how to use Node.js to create scripts
	- historically in a Linux environment one would use other languages for this, particularly bash scripts
	- traditionally one used any language that was installed, e.g. Perl, Ruby, Python, PHP, or more recently Rust or Go
	- a common use of scripts is to do file access tasks, e.g. backups, data converstion, etc.
	- commonly these scripts are not only run manually when needed but by cron jobs (Linux) or by automated task (Windows)
	- in the MERN stack it is very convenient to simply use Node for these tasks since it is the language which runs our servers as well
	- also since Node is installed with npm, it is common to wrap these tasks in npm scripts so that you have a central command "npm run" to start all tasks
