- **How we will build it**
	- we will set up a TypeScript React site
		- we will look at how basic types work in TypeScript
	- we will first simply display the fields in the JSX and manage the data inconguities with conditional rendering
		- we will realize that as our data expands in complexity, our JSX would become increasingly convoluted and error prone
	- the solution will be create TypeScript interface that defines which properties our objects should have
	- we will then **make a data-cleansing function** to convert the raw objects into objects defined by the TypeScript interface
	- our JSX will then no longer use the raw objects but **our JSX will use the objects defined by the TypeScript interface**
		- the advantage of this is that our **JSX will no longer need to manage the incongruities in the data**, and so will be cleaner, easier to read, and less error prone
	- we will define one of the properties as an **enum** that is allowed to only have a certain, pre-defined list of values
