	- **set up TypeScript up on the backend**
		- using TypeScript in the backend is not as easy as using TypeScrpt in the frontend
			- on the frontend, Vite sets everything up for us behind the scenes with the esbuild bundler
			- on the backend, we have to set everything up ourselves
				- this means we have toget everything to work with TypeScript and ES6 modules, both locally and at Heroku, which have their differences
					- locally, we need to start our `.ts` scripts with **ts-node** or to be precise, with **ts-node-esm** in order to use ES6 modules
					- Heroku, however, will execute JavaScript, i.e. the code created by the `npm run build` command, i.e. TypeScript transpiled into JavaScript
