- **What we will build**
	- Zustand is a new state manager that is simpler than the Redux and useContext/useReducer solutions to state management
		- Redux and useReducer, the reducer function is a pure function which cannot have side-effects
			- this makes it easier to test state, particularly in large, complex applications
			- this makes performing API calls together with state changes more complex
		- Zustand does not have the concept of reducer as pure function
			- therefore you can create an endless list of **actions** on one object **store** that is available everywhere in your application
				- these actions can perform both API calls and state changes
			- for all but the most complex applications, Zustand is a very practical solution to state management
			- even for complex applications, testing could be accomplished in other ways, e.g. 
				- using TypeScript to guarantee type safety
				- unit testing (Jest, Vitest)
				- component testing (Enzyme, React Testing Library)
				- end-to-end testing (Cypress)
		- therefore, my advice is to use Zustand for state management in most React sites
