- **What we will build:**
	- this is a plain vanilla site: HTML, CSS and JavaScript files
	- we have a main.js file that uses ES6 modules to load data in order to display
	- there are two data modules which are loaded
		- **books.js** which simply returns a JavaScript array of books
		- **techBooks.js** which uses `fetch` to load books via an external API
			- this module of course has to use a Promise since it is loading asynchronous data
- **Why build this site?**
	- this shows you how you can organize a JS/DOM application with modern ES6 modules which load async data via the Internet
	- it uses no **framework** (React, Angular, Vue) or **bundler** (Webpack, Parcel) or **task runner** (Gulp) or **build tool** (Vite, create-react-app)
	- in this way, it shows you the simple skills to create quite robust applications with only HTML, CSS and JavaScript
