- **(1) what we will learn**
	- how to perform CRUD with fetch and axios
		- CRUD = **C**react, **R*ead, **U**pdate, **D**elete
	- for this we need to have a backend which responds to the main REST verbs:
		- **GET** = fetch data
		- **POST** = add data
		- **PUT** = replace data (usually an entire object)
		- **PATCH** = replace some data (e.g. only one property of an object)
		- **DELETE** = remove data
	- one way to demonstrate how to use REST verbs would be to
		- create our own local backend with **Node/Express**
		- but this would be take a lot of effort to create all REST routes to support CRUD actions
	- much easier for our purposes is to use **[json-server](https://www.npmjs.com/package/json-server)** which
		- runs on a dedicated local port just like a typical Node/Express backend
		- allows you to send requests with REST verbs to GET, POST, PUT, PATCH and DELETE objects in arrays contained in one JSON file
		- allows you to set up a **full REST backend API** in a few minutes
		- while json-server is not recommended for online production sites (since it lacks authentication/authorization rules)
			- it is an **good tool** to create **local web applications** to **display/add/edit/delete** data in a JSON file
			- it is a **good academic tool** to learn how to use a **REST API** from your frontend
	- **code is here**
		- https://github.com/edwardtanguay/et882-vite-rest-json-server
