- this howto demonstrates that
	- using the **spread operator** to copy an object creates only a **shallow copy**
	- using **structuredClone()** to copy an object creates a **true deep clone**
	- example code can be run in Node and in the browser
	- **[structuredClone()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/structuredClone)** is available as of **17.0.0 (Released 2021-10-19)**
- code is here:
	- https://github.com/edwardtanguay/et881-deep-clone-test
- demonstration:#gif#thedemoofstructurdclone
- **tools.js**
	-------------------------------------------
	export const getClone = (obj) => {

		// pointers to the same object
		// const obj2 = obj; 

		// a shallow copy, deep values remain pointers to the original object
		// const obj2 = { ...obj };

		// A TRUE DEEP CLONE 
		const obj2 = structuredClone(obj);	

		return obj2;
	};	
	-------------------------------------------
